# Module library

Files here register reusable modules; they do not build machine configs. Host files (`modules/hosts/<host>/default.nix`) assemble outputs.

**Belongs here:**
- Register one or more modules into `flake.modules.{nixos,darwin,homeManager}.<camelName>`.
- **feature** = one concern (a service, program, or package set); localize its own effects (`age.secrets`, `systemd.services`, `home.packages`).
- **bundle** = compose features via `imports = with <class>Mods; [ … ];`.
- New `options.my.*` go in the relevant `base.nix` only.

**Belongs in host wiring (not here):**
- Choosing which modules a machine gets and setting `my.*` (hostName, homeImports, authorizedKeys, …).
- Per-machine values (IPs, firewall ports, fileSystems).

**Conventions:**
- File names are kebab-case; registered module names are camelCase (`gapuchi-terminal.nix` → `gapuchiTerminal`).
- Reference siblings via `let nixosMods = config.flake.modules.nixos; in … imports = with nixosMods; [ … ];`.
- External-flake packages: `inputs.<name>.packages.${pkgs.stdenv.hostPlatform.system}.default`.
- Don't read `my.*` to branch behavior by host — keep features generic.
- Respect machine categories (no GUI packages on server/macOS targets).
